| VFMIS | | | | | | vd |
| VFDIV | | | | | | vd |

### Conflict Summary

**Highest-conflict pairs (avoid for dual-issue):**
- VALU + VMAC: share read ports 0, 1, 2 on all three operands -> 3 read conflicts
- VALU + VMAC2: same as above
- VFMIS + VLSU: share read ports 4 (VFMIS-vs1, VLSU-vs2) and 5 (VFMIS-vs2, VLSU-vs3)
- VALU + VLSU: share write port 0

**Low-conflict pairs (prefer for dual-issue):**
- Scalar + any vector: scalar uses no VRF ports -> zero conflict
- VALU + VFMIS: read ports 0-2 vs 3-5 (no overlap); write 0 vs 5 (no overlap) -> clean
- VFMIS + VMAC: read ports 3-5 vs 0-2 (no overlap); write 5 vs 3 (no overlap) -> clean
- VMAC + VLSU: read ports 0-2 vs 4-5 (no overlap); write 3 vs 0 (no overlap) -> clean
  (VLSU as second satisfies restriction 3 from 23.15.1)

